obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1368)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1368&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Civil`
  line `Liability for Nuclear Damage Act, 2010.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It also applies to nuclear damage suffered--`
  line
  line `(a) in or over the maritime areas beyond the territorial waters of India;`
  line
  line `(b) in or over the exclusive economic zone of India as referred to in section 7 of the Territorial`
  line `Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and Other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of`
  line `1976);`
  line
  line `(c) on board or by a ship registered in India under section 22 of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958`
  line `(44 of 1958) or under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(d) on board or by an aircraft registered in India under clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 5 of`
  line `the Aircraft Act, 1934 (22 of 1934) or under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(e) on or by an artificial island, installation or structure under the jurisdiction of India.`
  line
  line `(4) It applies only to the nuclear installation owned or controlled by the Central Government either by`
  line `itself or through any authority or corporation established by it or a Government company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "Government company" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause (bb) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Atomic Energy Act, 1962`
  line `(33 of 1962).`
  line
  line `(5) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint; and`
  line `different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and any reference in any such`
  line `provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming into force of`
  line `that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 11th November, 2011, vide notification No. S.O. 2526(E), dated 11th November, 2011, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1369)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1369&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Commission appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(b) "Claims Commissioner" means the Claims Commissioner appointed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) "Commission" means the Nuclear Damage Claims Commission established under section 19;`
  line
  line `(d) "environment" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of section 2 of the`
  line `Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(e) "Member" means a Member of the Commission appointed under sub-section (1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the term "notify" shall`
  line `be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(g) "nuclear damage'' means--`
  line
  line `(i) loss of life or personal injury (including immediate and long term health impact) to a`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) loss of, or damage to, property,`
  line
  line `caused by or arising out of a nuclear incident, and includes each of the following to the extent`
  line `notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) any economic loss, arising from the loss or damage referred to in sub-clauses (i) or (ii)`
  line `and not included in the claims made under those sub-clauses, if incurred by a person entitled to`
  line `claim such loss or damage;`
  line
  line `(iv) costs of measures of reinstatement of impaired environment caused by a nuclear incident,`
  line `unless such impairment is insignificant, if such measures are actually taken or to be taken and not`
  line `included in the claims made under sub-clause (ii);`
  line
  line `(v) loss of income derived from an economic interest in any use or enjoyment of the`
  line `environment, incurred as a result of a significant impairment of that environment caused by a`
  line `nuclear incident, and not included in the claims under sub-clause (ii);`
  line
  line `(vi) the costs of preventive measures, and further loss or damage caused by such measures;`
  line
  line `(vii) any other economic loss, other than the one caused by impairment of the environment`
  line `referred to in sub-clauses (iv) and (v), in so far as it is permitted by the general law on civil`
  line `liability in force in India and not claimed under any such law,`
  line
  line `in the case of sub-clauses (i) to (v) and (vii) above, to the extent the loss or damage arises out of, or results`
  line `from, ionizing radiation emitted by any source of radiation inside a nuclear installation, or emitted from`
  line `nuclear fuel or radioactive products or waste in, or of, nuclear material coming from, originating in, or`
  line `sent to, a nuclear installation, whether so arising from the radioactive properties of such matter, or from a`
  line `combination of radioactive properties with toxic, explosive or other hazardous properties of such matter;`
  line
  line `(h) "nuclear fuel" means any material which is capable of producing energy by a self-sustaining chain`
  line `process of nuclear fission;`
  line
  line `(i) "nuclear incident" means any occurrence or series of occurrences having the same origin which`
  line `causes nuclear damage or, but only with respect to preventive measures, creates a grave and imminent`
  line `threat of causing such damage;`
  line
  line `(j) "nuclear installation" means--`
  line
  line `(A) any nuclear reactor other than one with which a means of transport is equipped for use as a`
  line `source of power, whether for propulsion thereof or for any other purpose;`
  line
  line `(B) any facility using nuclear fuel for the production of nuclear material, or any facility for the`
  line `processing of nuclear material, including re-processing of irradiated nuclear fuel; and`
  line
  line `(C) any facility where nuclear material is stored (other than storage incidental to the carriage of`
  line `such material).`
  line
  line `"Explanation".--For the purpose of this clause, several nuclear installations of one operator which are`
  line `located at the same site shall be considered as a single nuclear installation;`
  line
  line `(k) "nuclear material" means and includes`
  line
  line `(i) nuclear fuel (other than natural uranium or depleted uranium) capable of producing energy by`
  line `a self-sustaining chain process of nuclear fission outside a nuclear reactor, either by itself or in`
  line `combination with some other material; and`
  line
  line `(ii) radioactive products or waste;`
  line
  line `(l) "nuclear reactor" means any structure containing nuclear fuel in such an arrangement that a selfsustaining`
  line `chain process of nuclear fission can occur therein without an additional source of neutrons;`
  line
  line `(m) "operator", in relation to a nuclear installation, means the Central Government or any authority or`
  line `corporation established by it or a Government company who has been granted a licence pursuant to the`
  line `Atomic Energy Act, 1962 (33 of 1962) for the operation of that installation;`
  line
  line `(n) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "preventive measures" means any reasonable measures taken by a person after a nuclear incident`
  line `has occurred to prevent or minimise damage referred to in sub-clauses (i) to (v) and (vii) of clause (g),`
  line `subject to the approval of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(p) "radioactive products or waste" means any radioactive material produced in, or any material made`
  line `radioactive by exposure to, the radiation incidental to the production or utilisation of nuclear fuel, but`
  line `does not include radioisotopes which have reached the final stage of fabrication so as to be usable for any`
  line `scientific, medical, agricultural, commercial or industrial purpose;`
  line
  line `(q) "Special Drawing Rights" means Special Drawing Rights as determined by the International`
  line `Monetary Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1370)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Atomic Energy Regulatory Board to notify nuclear incident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1370&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Atomic Energy`
  line `Regulatory Board constituted under the Atomic Energy Act, 1962 (33 of 1962) shall, within a period of`
  line `fifteen days from the date of occurrence of a nuclear incident, notify such nuclear incident:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Atomic Energy Regulatory Board is satisfied that the gravity of threat and`
  line `risk involved in a nuclear incident is insignificant, it shall not be required to notify such nuclear incident.`
  line
  line `(2) The Atomic Energy Regulatory Board shall, immediately after the notification under sub-section`
  line `(1) is issued, cause wide publicity to be given to the occurrence of such nuclear incident, in such manner`
  line `as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1371)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Liability of operator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1371&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The operator of the nuclear installation shall be liable for nuclear`
  line `damage caused by a nuclear incident--`
  line
  line `(a) in that nuclear installation; or`
  line
  line `(b) involving nuclear material coming from, or originating in, that nuclear installation and`
  line `occurring before--`
  line
  line `(i) the liability for nuclear incident involving such nuclear material has been assumed,`
  line `pursuant to a written agreement, by another operator; or`
  line
  line `(ii) another operator has taken charge of such nuclear material; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the person duly authorised to operate a nuclear reactor has taken charge of the nuclear`
  line `material intended to be used in that reactor with which means of transport is equipped for use as a`
  line `source of power, whether for propulsion thereof or for any other purpose; or`
  line
  line `(iv) such nuclear material has been unloaded from the means of transport by which it was sent`
  line `to a person within the territory of a foreign State; or`
  line
  line `(c) involving nuclear material sent to that nuclear installation and occurring after--`
  line
  line `(i) the liability for nuclear incident involving such nuclear material has been transferred to`
  line `that operator, pursuant to a written agreement, by the operator of another nuclear installation; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that operator has taken charge of such nuclear material; or`
  line
  line `(iii) that operator has taken charge of such nuclear material from a person operating a nuclear`
  line `reactor with which a means of transport is equipped for use as a source of power, whether for`
  line `propulsion thereof or for any other purpose; or`
  line
  line `(iv) such nuclear material has been loaded, with the written consent of that operator, on the`
  line `means of transport by which it is to be carried from the territory of a foreign State.`
  line
  line `(2) Where more than one operator is liable for nuclear damage, the liability of the operators so`
  line `involved shall, in so far as the damage attributable to each operator is not separable, be joint and several:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total liability of such operators shall not exceed the extent of liability specified`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 6.`
  line
  line `(3) Where several nuclear installations of one and the same operator are involved in a nuclear`
  line `incident, such operator shall, in respect of each such nuclear installation, be liable to the extent of liability`
  line `specified under sub-section (2) of section 6.`
  line
  line `(4) The liability of the operator of the nuclear installation shall be strict and shall be based on the`
  line `principle of no-fault liability.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) where nuclear damage is caused by a nuclear incident occurring in a nuclear installation on`
  line `account of temporary storage of material-in-transit in such installation, the person responsible for`
  line `transit of such material shall be deemed to be the operator;`
  line
  line `(b) where a nuclear damage is caused as a result of nuclear incident during the transportation of`
  line `nuclear material, the consignor shall be deemed to be the operator;`
  line
  line `(c) where any written agreement has been entered into between the consignor and the consignee`
  line `or, as the case may be, the consignor and the carrier of nuclear material, the person liable for any`
  line `nuclear damage under such agreement shall be deemed to be the operator;`
  line
  line `(d) where both nuclear damage and damage other than nuclear damage have been caused by a`
  line `nuclear incident or, jointly by a nuclear incident and one or more other occurrences, such other`
  line `damage shall, to the extent it is not separable from the nuclear damage, be deemed to be a nuclear`
  line `damage caused by such nuclear incident.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1372)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Operator not liable in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1372&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) An operator shall not be liable for any nuclear`
  line `damage where such damage is caused by a nuclear incident directly due to-`
  line
  line `(i) a grave natural disaster of an exceptional character; or`
  line
  line `(ii) an act of armed conflict, hostility, civil war, insurrection or terrorism.`
  line
  line `(2) An operator shall not be liable for any nuclear damage caused to--`
  line
  line `(i) the nuclear installation itself and any other nuclear installation including a nuclear installation`
  line `under construction, on the site where such installation is located; and`
  line
  line `(ii) to any property on the same site which is used or to be used in connection with any such`
  line `installation; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to the means of transport upon which the nuclear material involved was carried at the time of`
  line `nuclear incident:`
  line
  line `Provided that any compensation liable to be paid by an operator for a nuclear damage shall not`
  line `have the effect of reducing the amount of his liability in respect of any other claim for damage under`
  line `any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any nuclear damage is suffered by a person on account of his own negligence or from his`
  line `own acts of commission or omission, the operator shall not be liable to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1373)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Limits of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1373&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The maximum amount of liability in respect of each nuclear incident shall`
  line `be the rupee equivalent of three hundred million Special Drawing Rights or such higher amount as the`
  line `Central Government may specify by notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may take additional measures, where necessary, if the`
  line `compensation to be awarded under this Act exceeds the amount specified under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The liability of an operator for each nuclear incident shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of nuclear reactors having thermal power equal to or above ten MW, rupees one`
  line `thousand five hundred crores;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of spent fuel reprocessing plants, rupees three hundred crores;`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of the research reactors having thermal power below ten MW, fuel cycle facilities`
  line `other than spent fuel reprocessing plants and transportation of nuclear materials, rupees one hundred`
  line `crores:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may review the amount of operator's liability from time to`
  line `time and specify, by notification, a higher amount under this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the amount of liability shall not include any interest or cost of proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1374)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Liability of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1374&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall be liable for nuclear damage`
  line `in respect of a nuclear incident,`
  line
  line `(a) where the liability exceeds the amount of liability of an operator specified under sub-section (2) of section 6, to the extent such liability exceeds such liability of the operator;`
  line
  line `(b) occurring in a nuclear installation owned by it; and`
  line
  line `(c) occurring on account of causes specified in clauses (i) and (ii) of sub-section (1) of section 5:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, assume full liability for a nuclear`
  line `installation not operated by it if it is of the opinion that it is necessary in public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of meeting part of its liability under clause (a) or clause (c) of sub-section (1), the Central Government may establish a fund to be called the Nuclear Liability Fund by charging such`
  line `amount of levy from the operators, in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1375)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Operator to maintain insurance or financial securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1375&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The operator shall, before he begins`
  line `operation of his nuclear installation, take out insurance policy or such other financial security or`
  line `combination of both, covering his liability under sub-section (2) of section 6, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The operator shall from time to time renew the insurance policy or other financial security`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), before the expiry of the period of validity thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall not apply to a nuclear installation owned by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "financial security" means a contract of indemnity or`
  line `guarantee, or shares or bonds or such instrument as may be prescribed or any combination thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1376)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Compensation for nuclear damage and its adjudication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1376&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever suffers nuclear damage`
  line `shall be entitled to claim compensation in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of adjudicating upon claims for compensation in respect of nuclear damage, the`
  line `Central Government shall, by notification, appoint one or more Claims Commissioners for such area, as`
  line `may be specified in that notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1377)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1377&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified for`
  line `appointment as a Claims Commissioner unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, a District Judge; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the service of the Central Government and has held the post not below the rank of`
  line `Additional Secretary to the Government of India or any other equivalent post in the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1378)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1378&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line The
  line `salary and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service of Claims Commissioner shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1379)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Adjudication procedure and powers of Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1379&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of`
  line `adjudication of claims under this Act, the Claims Commissioner shall follow such procedure as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of holding inquiry, the Claims Commissioner may associate with him such`
  line `persons having expertise in the nuclear field or such other persons and in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Where any person is associated under sub-section (2), he shall be paid such remuneration, fee or`
  line `allowance, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Claims Commissioner shall, for the purposes of discharging his functions under this Act,`
  line `have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908),`
  line `while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing of commission for the examination of any witness;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Claims Commissioner shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and`
  line `Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1380)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Inviting application for claims by Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1380&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `After the notification of nuclear`
  line `incident under sub-section (1) of section 3, the Claims Commissioner, having jurisdiction over the area,`
  line `shall cause wide publicity to be given, in such manner as he deems fit, for inviting applications for`
  line `claiming compensation for nuclear damage.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1381)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Person entitled to make application for nuclear damage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1381&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `An application for compensation`
  line `before the Claims Commissioner or the Commission, as the case may be, in respect of nuclear damage`
  line `may be made by--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has sustained injury; or`
  line
  line `(b) the owner of the property to which damage has been caused; or`
  line
  line `(c) the legal representatives of the deceased; or`
  line
  line `(d) any agent duly authorised by such person or owner or legal representatives.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1382)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Procedure for making application before Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1382&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for`
  line `compensation before the Claims Commissioner for nuclear damage shall be made in such form,`
  line `containing such particulars and accompanied by such documents, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 18, every application under sub-section (1) shall be made`
  line `within a period of three years from the date of knowledge of nuclear damage by the person suffering such`
  line damage.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1383)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Award by Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1383&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15, the Claims Commissioner shall, after giving notice of such application to the operator and`
  line `affording an opportunity of being heard to the parties, dispose of the application within a period of three`
  line `months from the date of such receipt and make an award accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) While making an award under this section, the Claims Commissioner shall not take into`
  line `consideration any benefit, reimbursement or amount received by the applicant in pursuance of contract of`
  line `insurance taken by him or for members of his family or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an operator is likely to remove or dispose of his property with the object of evading`
  line `payment by him of the amount of the award, the Claims Commissioner may, in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of rules 1 to 4 of Order XXXIX of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5`
  line `of 1908), grant a temporary injunction to restrain such act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Claims Commissioner shall arrange to deliver copies of the award to the parties within a`
  line `period of fifteen days from the date of the award.`
  line
  line `(5) Every award made under sub-section (1) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1384)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Operator's right of recourse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1384&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The operator of the nuclear installation, after paying the`
  line `compensation for nuclear damage in accordance with section 6, shall have a right of recourse where--`
  line
  line `(a) such right is expressly provided for in a contract in writing;`
  line
  line `(b) the nuclear incident has resulted as a consequence of an act of supplier or his employee, which`
  line `includes supply of equipment or material with patent or latent defects or sub-standard services;`
  line
  line `(c) the nuclear incident has resulted from the act of commission or omission of an individual done`
  line `with the intent to cause nuclear damage.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1385)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Extinction of right to claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1385&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The right to claim compensation for nuclear damage shall`
  line `extinguish, if such claim is not made within a period of--`
  line
  line `(a) ten years, in the case of damage to property;`
  line
  line `(b) twenty years, in the case of personal injury to any person,`
  line `from the date of occurrence of the incident notified under sub-section (1) of section 3:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a nuclear damage is caused by a nuclear incident involving nuclear material`
  line `which, prior to such nuclear incident, had been stolen, lost, jettisoned or abandoned, the said period of ten`
  line `years shall be computed from the date of such nuclear incident, but, in no case, it shall exceed a period of`
  line `twenty years from the date of such theft, loss, jettison or abandonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1386)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Establishment of Nuclear Damage Claims Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1386&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where the Central Government,`
  line `having regard to the injury or damage caused by a nuclear incident, is of the opinion that it is expedient in`
  line `public interest that such claims for such damage be adjudicated by the Commission instead of a Claims`
  line `Commissioner, it may, by notification, establish a Commission for the purpose of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1387)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Composition of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1387&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall consist of a Chairperson and such other`
  line `Members, not exceeding six, as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and other Members of the Commission shall be appointed on the`
  line `recommendation of a Selection Committee consisting of three experts from amongst the persons having at`
  line `least thirty years of experience in nuclear science and a retired Supreme Court Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Chairperson of the Commission unless he`
  line `has attained the age of fifty-five years and is or has been or qualified to be a Judge of a High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appointment of a sitting judge shall be made except after consultation with the Chief`
  line `Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(4) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Member unless he has attained the age of`
  line `fifty-five years and--`
  line
  line `(a) has held or is holding or qualified to hold, the post of Additional Secretary to the Government`
  line `of India or any other equivalent post in the Central Government and possesses special knowledge in`
  line `law relating to nuclear liability arising out of nuclear incident; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been a Claims Commissioner for five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1388)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1388&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or a Member, as the case may be, shall hold office as such for a`
  line `term of three years from the date on which he enters upon his office and shall be eligible for reappointment`
  line `for another term of three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall hold office as such Chairperson or Member after he has attained the age`
  line `of sixty-seven years.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1389)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1389&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The salary and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service, including pension,`
  line `gratuity and other retirement benefits, of the Chairperson and other Members shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson or`
  line `other Members shall be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1390)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Filling up of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1390&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If, for reasons other than temporary absence, any vacancy occurs in the`
  line `office of the Chairperson or Member, as the case may be, the Central Government shall appoint another`
  line `person in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy and the proceedings may be`
  line `continued before the Commission from the stage at which it was, before the vacancy is filled.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1391)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1391&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson or a Member may, by a notice in writing under`
  line `his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or the Member shall, unless he is permitted by the Central Government`
  line `to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date of`
  line `receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or until the`
  line `expiry of his term of office, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall remove from office the Chairperson or a Member who--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office detrimental to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Member shall be removed under clause (d) or clause (e) unless he has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1392)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Chairperson or Member deemed to retire from service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1392&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `A person who, immediately before`
  line `the date of assuming office as a Chairperson or a Member, was in service of the Government, shall be`
  line `deemed to have retired from service on the date on which he enters upon office as such, but his`
  line `subsequent service as the Chairperson or a Member shall be reckoned as continuing approved service`
  line `counting for pension in service to which he belonged.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1393)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Suspension of pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1393&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `If a person who, immediately before the date of assuming office as the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member was in receipt of or being eligible so to do, has opted to draw, a pension, other`
  line `than a disability or wound pension, in respect of any previous service under the Central Government, his`
  line `salary in respect of service as the Chairperson or a Member shall be reduced--`
  line
  line `(a) by the amount of that pension; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he had, before assuming office, received, in lieu of a portion of the pension due to him in`
  line `respect of such previous service, the commuted value thereof, by the amount of that portion of the`
  line pension.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1394)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Prohibition of acting as arbitrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1394&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, while holding office as a Chairperson or a`
  line `Member, act as an arbitrator in any matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1395)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Prohibition of practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1395&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `On ceasing to hold office, the Chairperson or a Member shall not`
  line `appear, act or plead before the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1396)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Powers of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1396&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall have the power of superintendence in the general`
  line `administration of the Commission and exercise such powers as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1397)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Officers and other employees of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1397&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall provide the`
  line `Commission with such officers and other employees as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The salary and allowances payable to and the terms and other conditions of service of officers and`
  line `other employees of the Commission shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1398)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Application for compensation before Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1398&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for compensation`
  line `before the Commission for nuclear damage shall be made in such form, containing such particulars and`
  line `accompanied by such documents, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 18, every application under sub-section (1) shall be made`
  line `within a period of three years from the date of knowledge of nuclear damage by the person suffering such`
  line damage.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1399)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Adjudication procedure and powers of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1399&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall have original`
  line `jurisdiction to adjudicate upon every application for compensation filed before it under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 31 or transferred to it under section 33, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon transfer of cases to the Commission under section 33, the Commission shall hear such`
  line `applications from the stage at which it was before such transfer.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson may constitute benches comprising of not more than three Members of the`
  line `Commission for the purpose of hearing of claims and any decision thereon shall be rendered by a majority`
  line `of the Members hearing such claims.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall not be bound by the procedure laid down in the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908) but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and subject to the other provisions`
  line `of this Act and of any rules made thereunder, the Commission shall have the power to regulate its own`
  line `procedure including the places and the times at which it shall have its sittings.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908, (5 of 1908) while trying a`
  line `suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing of commission for the examination of any witness;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall, after giving notice of application to the operator and after affording an`
  line `opportunity of being heard to the parties, dispose of such application within a period of three months from`
  line `the date of such receipt and make an award accordingly.`
  line
  line `(7) While making an award under this section, the Commission shall not take into consideration any`
  line `benefit, reimbursement or amount received by the applicant in pursuance of any contract of insurance or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `(8) Where an operator is likely to remove or dispose of his property with the object of evading`
  line `payment by him of the amount of the award, the Commission may, in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `rules 1 to 4 of Order XXXIX of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), grant`
  line `a temporary injunction to restrain such act.`
  line
  line `(9) The Commission shall arrange to deliver copies of the award to the parties concerned within a`
  line `period of fifteen days from the date of such award.`
  line
  line `(10) Every award made under sub-section (6) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (1400)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Transfer of pending cases to Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1400&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Every application for compensation pending before`
  line `the Claims Commissioner immediately before the date of establishment of the Commission under section`
  line `19 shall stand transferred on that date to the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (1401)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Proceedings before Claims Commissioner or Commission to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1401&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `proceeding before the Claims Commissioner or the Commission under this Act shall be deemed to be`
  line `judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193, 219 and 228 of, and for the purposes of section`
  line `196 of, the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (1402)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Exclusion of jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1402&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in section 46, no civil court`
  line `(except the Supreme Court and a High Court exercising jurisdiction under articles 226 and 227 of the`
  line `Constitution) shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceedings in respect of any matter which the`
  line `Claims Commissioner or the Commission, as the case may be, is empowered to adjudicate under this Act`
  line `and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be`
  line `taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (1403)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Enforcement of awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1403&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an award is made under sub-section (1) of section 16 or`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 32,`
  line
  line `(a) the insurer or any person, as the case may be, who under the contract of insurance or financial`
  line `security under section 8 is required to pay any amount in terms of such award and to the extent of his`
  line `liability under such contract, shall deposit that amount within such time and in such manner as the`
  line `Claims Commissioner or the Commission, as the case may be, may direct; and`
  line
  line `(b) the operator shall, subject to the maximum liability specified under sub-section (2) of section`
  line `6, deposit the remaining amount by which such award exceeds the amount deposited under clause (a).`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person referred to in sub-section (1) fails to deposit the amount of award within the`
  line `period specified in the award, such amount shall be recoverable from such person as arrears of land`
  line revenue.
  line
  line `(3) The amount deposited under sub-section (1) shall be disbursed to such person as may be specified`
  line `in the award within a period of fifteen days from the date of such deposit.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (1404)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1404&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial`
  line `year, as may be prescribed, an annual report giving full account of its activities during that financial year`
  line `and submit a copy thereof to the Central Government which shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (1405)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Dissolution of Commission in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1405&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied that the purpose for which the Commission established under section 19 has served its purpose,`
  line `or where the number of cases pending before such Commission is so less that it would not justify the cost`
  line `of its continued function, or where it considers necessary or expedient so to do, the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, dissolve the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) With effect from the date of notification of dissolution of Commission under sub-section (1),`
  line
  line `(a) the proceeding, if any, pending before the Commission as on the date of such notification`
  line `shall be transferred to the Claims Commissioner to be appointed by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairperson and all Members of the Commission shall be deemed to have vacated their`
  line `offices as such and they shall not be entitled to any compensation for premature termination of their`
  line office;
  line
  line `(c) officers and other employees of the Commission shall be transferred to such other authority or`
  line `offices of the Central Government, in such manner, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the officers and other employees so transferred, shall be entitled to the same terms`
  line `and conditions of service as would have been held by them in the Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where an officer or an employee of the Commission refuses to join the`
  line `services in such other authority or office, he shall be deemed to have resigned and shall not be entitled`
  line `to any compensation for premature termination of contract of service;`
  line
  line `(d) all assets and liabilities of the Commission shall vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the dissolution of the Commission under sub-section (1), anything done or any`
  line `action taken or purported to have been done or taken including any order made or notice issued or any`
  line `appointment, confirmation or declaration made or any document or instrument executed or any direction`
  line `given by the Commission before such dissolution, shall be deemed to have been validly done or taken.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be construed to prevent the Central Government to establish the`
  line `Commission subsequent to the dissolution of the Commission in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (1406)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1406&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes any rule made or any direction issued under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to comply with the provisions of section 8; or`
  line
  line `(c) fails to deposit the amount under section 36,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years or with fine or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever fails to comply with any direction issued under section 43 or obstructs any authority or`
  line `person in the exercise of his powers under this Act shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (1407)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1407&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company,`
  line `every person who at the time the offence was committed, was directly in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment under this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (1408)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Offences by Government Departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1408&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Where an offence under this Act has been committed`
  line `by any Department of the Government, the Head of the Department shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render such Head of the Department liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (1409)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1409&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class shall try any offence under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that cognizance of such offence shall not be taken except on a complaint made by the`
  line `Central Government or any authority or officer authorised in this behalf by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (1410)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1410&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, in exercise of its powers and`
  line `performance of its functions under this Act, issue such directions, as it may deem fit, for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, to any operator, person, officer, authority or body and such operator, person, officer, authority or`
  line `body shall be bound to comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (1411)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1411&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may call for such information from an`
  line `operator as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (1412)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Exemption from application of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1412&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, exempt`
  line `any nuclear installation from the application of this Act where, having regard to small quantity of nuclear`
  line `material, it is of the opinion that the risk involved is insignificant.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (1413)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Act to be in addition to any other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1413&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, any other law for the time being in force, and nothing contained herein shall exempt`
  line `the operator from any proceeding which might, apart from this Act, be instituted against such operator.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (1414)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1414&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the person, officer or authority in respect of anything done by it or`
  line `him in good faith in pursuance of this Act or of any rule or order made, or direction issued, thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (1415)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1415&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for carrying`
  line `out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers such rules may`
  line `provide for --`
  line
  line `(a) the other financial security and the manner thereof under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the salary and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of Claims`
  line
  line `Commissioner under section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed by Claims Commissioner under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) the person to be associated by Claims Commissioner and the manner thereof, under subsection`
  line `(2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the remuneration, fee or allowances of associated person under sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter under clause (f) of sub-section (4) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of application, the particulars it shall contain and the documents it shall accompany,`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(h) the salary and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service of Chairperson`
  line `and other Members, under section 22;`
  line
  line `(i) the powers of Chairperson under section 29;`
  line
  line `(j) the salary and allowances payable to and the terms and other conditions of service of officers`
  line `and other employees of the Commission, under sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(k) the form of application, the particulars it shall contain and the documents it shall accompany,`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter under clause (f) of sub-section (5) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and the time for preparing annual report by the Commission under section 37;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of transfer of officers and other employees of the Commission under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 38.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (1416)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224&sectionId=1416&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_38_63_00002_201038_1517807327224
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
